# Architecture Rules — {{PROJECT_NAME}}

## Before Any Structural Change

1. Read `docs/architecture.md` and `project-structure.md`
2. Write ADR in `docs/decisions.md` using the template
3. Obtain explicit human approval
4. Update architecture docs after implementation

## Module Boundaries

- Presentation → Application → Domain → Infrastructure (one direction)
- Domain must not import from infrastructure
- Shared utilities go in `src/shared/` — not duplicated across modules

## Dependencies

- Prefer stable, well-maintained libraries
- Justify new dependencies in ADR or PR description
- Pin versions in lockfile

## Scalability Defaults

- Stateless services where possible
- Idempotent handlers for retriable operations
- Explicit timeouts on external calls

## Prohibited

- Circular module dependencies
- God files (>400 lines without clear justification)
- Architecture changes bundled silently in feature PRs
